	<p>
		Beevish Hospital’s Neurology Department is dedicated to the diagnosis and treatment of disorders affecting the brain, spinal cord, and nervous system. With a team of expert neurologists, this department utilizes cutting-edge technology to provide top-tier care for patients facing neurological conditions, ranging from epilepsy and migraines to complex disorders such as Parkinson's disease and multiple sclerosis.<br><br>

		The department is equipped with advanced diagnostic tools, including MRI, CT scans, and EEG monitoring, to facilitate accurate diagnosis and personalized treatment. The neurology team is committed to employing minimally invasive techniques when possible, ensuring both efficacy and patient comfort during treatments. Each patient receives a customized care plan tailored to their unique condition and medical history.<br><br>

		Preventive care is a cornerstone of the Neurology Department, with a focus on identifying early warning signs and risk factors for neurological diseases. Through screenings and regular check-ups, the team aims to prevent or delay the onset of neurological disorders. Additionally, the hospital’s rehabilitation services support patients in managing long-term neurological conditions.<br><br>

		Patient education and support are integral parts of the Neurology Department’s mission. The team regularly provides resources and counseling to help patients and their families understand the nature of neurological conditions and manage symptoms effectively. From lifestyle guidance to support groups, Beevish Hospital ensures holistic care.<br><br>

		Beevish Hospital’s Neurology Department is committed to staying at the forefront of neurological science. Through ongoing research, training, and professional development, the team continuously improves its approach to diagnosing, treating, and managing neurological conditions, reinforcing Beevish’s position as a leader in neurology.


